18(19) [edited]
<http://www.oie.int/eng/info/hebdo/a_current.htm#Sec5>

Sheep and goat pox in Viet Nam (disease never reported before in Viet Nam)
-------------------------------
Information received on 12 May 2005 (dated 2 May) from Dr Bui Quang Anh,
director, Department of Animal Health, Ministry of Agriculture and Rural
Development, Hanoi:
Reason for immediate notification: 1st occurrence of a listed disease or
infection in a country.
Date of 1st confirmation of the event: 5 Apr 2005.
Date of start of the event: 3 Jan 2005.
Nature of diagnosis: clinical, postmortem, and laboratory.
Details of outbreaks:
1.
1st administrative division: Cao Bang
Lower administrative division: Trung Khanh
Type of epidemiological unit: village
Name of the location: ...
Date of start of the outbreak: 3 Jan 2005
Species: cap
Number of animals in the outbreak:
susceptible / cases / deaths / destroyed / slaughtered
1000 / 598 / 515 / 83 / 0
2.
1st administrative division: Bac Giang
Lower administrative division: Luc Nam
Type of epidemiological unit: village
Name of the location: Dong Phu
Date of start of the outbreak: 13 Jan 2005
Species: cap
Number of animals in the outbreak:
susceptible / cases / deaths / destroyed / slaughtered
100 / 72 / 48 / 24 / 0
3.
1st administrative division: Bac Giang
Lower administrative division: Luc Nam
Type of epidemiological unit: village
Name of the location: Bien Son
Date of start of the outbreak: 13 Jan 2005
Species: cap
Number of animals in the outbreak:
susceptible / cases / deaths / destroyed /slaughtered
.. / ... / 170 / 0 / 0
4.
1st administrative division: Lang Son
Lower administrative division: Huu Lung
Type of epidemiological unit: village
Name of the location: ...
Date of start of the outbreak: 25 Jan 2005
Species: cap
Number of animals in the outbreak:
susceptible / cases / deaths / destroyed / slaughtered
65 / 31 / 1 / 30 / 0
5.
1st administrative division: Ha Tay
Lower administrative division: My Duc
Type of epidemiological unit: village
Name of the location: ...
Date of start of the outbreak: 18 Mar 2005
Species: cap
Number of animals in the outbreak:
susceptible / cases / deaths / destroyed / slaughtered
100 / 72 / 55 / 17 / 0
Diagnosis:
Laboratory where diagnosis was made: Institute for Animal Health, Pirbright
Laboratory (OIE Reference Laboratory for sheep pox and goat pox).
Species examined: cap
Diagnostic tests used: antigen detection, PCR (polymerase chain reaction).
Date: 5 Apr 2005.
Results: positive.
Source of outbreaks or origin of infection: illegal movement of animals.
Treatment of affected animals: Yes (symptomatic treatment of lesions).
